Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.96,0:00:08.36,Narrator,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,Once there was a man who obtained everything,\Nthe legendary Pirate King Gold Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.36,0:00:12.91,Narrator,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,His last words before he was executed inspired people to sail the seas.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.91,0:00:14.63,Gold,Roger,0000,0000,0000,,All my wealth and treasure?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.63,0:00:16.27,Gold,Roger,0000,0000,0000,,It can be yours if you want!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.27,0:00:17.42,Gold,Roger,0000,0000,0000,,Search for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.42,0:00:19.79,Gold,Roger,0000,0000,0000,,I left everything in that one place.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.79,0:00:22.82,Narrator,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,People now set sail in search of romance.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.82,0:00:25.40,Narrator,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,The world has entered a Great Age of Pirates!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.66,0:02:37.18,Narrator,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,All pirates who seek One Piece\Nstrive to reach the second half of the Grand Line...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.18,0:02:39.76,Narrator,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,The place called the New World.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.25,0:02:45.00,Narrator,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,And now, the boy who ate the Gomu Gomu Fruit\Nand became a rubber man,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.00,0:02:48.14,Narrator,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,Monkey D. Luffy and his crew\Nare going to challenge that sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.15,0:02:52.57,Main,Luffy,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna be the Pirate King!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.80,0:03:17.43,Narrator,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,In order to reach their next stage, the New World,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.43,0:03:20.54,Narrator,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,Luffy and the other Straw Hat Pirates have gone to Fishman Island,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.54,0:03:22.72,Narrator,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,located ten thousand meters under the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.72,0:03:29.48,Narrator,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,But there they find that the New Fishman Pirates\Nare planning to overthrow the Ryuuguu Kingdom,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.48,0:03:33.56,Narrator,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,and Vander Decken has been stalking the Mermaid Princess Shirahoshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.98,0:03:38.34,Narrator,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,The Straw Hat Pirates find themselves drawn into these events.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.62,0:03:40.87,Main,Fishmen,0000,0000,0000,,Boss!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.36,0:03:47.71,Main,Fishmen,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Boss!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.62,0:04:02.95,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,And so, the curtain fell on the life...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.95,0:04:08.49,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,of Fisher Tiger, captain of the Sun Pirates.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.90,0:04:13.43,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,The death of our captain...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.92,0:04:25.60,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have to tell you how much\Nthis hurt the crew that was left behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.06,0:04:39.42,Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you going?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.89,0:04:42.70,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,"Don't kill the humans"?!  What was he thinking?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.70,0:04:47.39,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,His pity for the humans is the reason he died!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.03,0:04:51.56,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,Brother Ti was a fool!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.83,0:04:53.98,Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Arlong-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.95,0:05:03.84,Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Arlong-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.84,0:05:07.16,Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Arlong-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.66,0:05:14.76,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,I will never forgive this!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.97,0:05:29.47,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,Prepare yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.47,0:05:31.61,Main,Marine,0000,0000,0000,,You're that fishman{\fscx250}-{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.40,0:05:41.48,Main,Kizaru,0000,0000,0000,,You're really noisy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.08,0:05:53.49,Main,Kizaru,0000,0000,0000,,So you're Arlong?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.09,0:05:56.75,Main,Kizaru,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you come back?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.75,0:05:58.54,Main,Kizaru,0000,0000,0000,,So recklessly... { def: originally "Just casually" } {Gil : nokonoko = without a care, unconcerndly. Either is good IMO.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.65,0:06:09.97,Main,Kizaru,0000,0000,0000,,coming back to this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.97,0:06:14.52,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,I came to slaughter the humans who shot Big Brother Ti!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.52,0:06:17.30,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to go to the island that sold us out too!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.30,0:06:19.65,Main,Kizaru,0000,0000,0000,,So this is your retaliation?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.65,0:06:22.87,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!  Fisher Tiger died!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.87,0:06:25.90,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,You inferior scumbags killed him!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.90,0:06:28.95,Main,Kizaru,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, really?  So he's dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.84,0:06:34.73,Main,Kizaru,0000,0000,0000,,Either way, you'll be coming with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.26,0:06:41.06,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,Fisher Tiger's death outraged Arlong,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.62,0:06:45.89,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,so he bared his fangs toward the humans he resented...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.89,0:06:48.13,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,and was captured.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.01,0:06:52.85,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,If the transfusion hadn't been refused, he could have survived!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.85,0:06:56.93,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,If we'd had access to fishman blood, Fisher Tiger wouldn't have died!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.40,0:07:01.98,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,You humans drove him to his death!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.85,0:07:10.68,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,"After being refused a blood transfusion by humans,\NFisher Tiger, captain of the Sun Pirates, died."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.27,0:07:13.76,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,It's not too far from the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.01,0:07:18.54,Main,Aladdin,0000,0000,0000,,It was the humans' fault that he died, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.08,0:07:22.00,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,Arlong lied to the Navy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.00,0:07:25.29,Main,Aladdin,0000,0000,0000,,The truth was much more cruel.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.29,0:07:32.43,Main,Aladdin,0000,0000,0000,,Resenting the humans that betrayed him,\Nthe hero Tiger refused to have their blood in his veins.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.43,0:07:34.87,Main,Aladdin,0000,0000,0000,,Not to mention his past as a slave.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.87,0:07:39.11,Main,Aladdin,0000,0000,0000,,If the world found out about that, it would damage the Boss's honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.73,0:07:42.38,Main,Aladdin,0000,0000,0000,,Arlong would never reveal that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.17,0:07:50.65,Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Nyuu- Captain Jinbe!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.65,0:07:52.15,Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Enemy ship sighted!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.15,0:07:55.99,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,Even if the Boss is gone, we cannot turn back now!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.42,0:08:02.40,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,Prepare for battle!  But remember, don't kill anyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.40,0:08:05.63,Main,Fishmen,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.31,0:08:11.12,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,I became known as Sea Knight Jinbe,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.12,0:08:14.78,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,captain of the Sun Pirates.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.78,0:08:18.28,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,I devoted myself to never-ending battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.10,0:08:23.35,Main,Neptune,0000,0000,0000,,"I am writing this to you...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.35,0:08:27.77,Main,Neptune,0000,0000,0000,,because I feel you deserve to know the whole truth."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.69,0:08:32.74,Main,Neptune,0000,0000,0000,,"Captain of the Sun Pirates, Jinbe."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.73,0:08:35.66,Flashbacks,Tiger,0000,0000,0000,,I've made up my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.20,0:08:40.66,Main,Neptune,0000,0000,0000,,So Tiger was forced to choose the path he took -jamon.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.61,0:08:46.13,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,Now I understand the scream I heard from his heart that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.93,0:09:03.47,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,I will be alright.  I will not lose!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.38,0:09:06.72,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,We must live beneath the sun!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.72,0:09:09.65,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,The day when we and the humans understand each other will definitely come!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.65,0:09:13.37,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,Sign this form!  Declare your wish to emigrate, here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.37,0:09:16.50,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,I can't!  It's impossible, Otohime-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.97,0:09:22.10,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,Tiger-san saved all the slaves,\Nhe didn't discriminate by race...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.10,0:09:24.49,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,but then the humans simply abandoned him!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.49,0:09:26.04,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,Just how are we supposed to understand one another?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.64,0:09:33.09,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,Not a single signature today, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.55,0:09:35.91,Main,Princes,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.91,0:09:37.55,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,My children!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.59,0:09:43.38,Main,Shirahoshi,0000,0000,0000,,Mother, are you alright?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.38,0:09:46.33,Main,Princes,0000,0000,0000,,Are you alright?  Are you alright?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.33,0:09:48.81,Main,Fukaboshi,0000,0000,0000,,She's completely worn out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.81,0:09:52.49,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, my oasis of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.09,0:09:55.65,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,I am alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.91,0:09:58.07,Main,Shirahoshi,0000,0000,0000,,Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.51,0:09:59.87,Main,Princes,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.64,0:10:02.58,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,Let us make a promise...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.63,0:10:06.00,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,for your future.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.94,0:10:12.80,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,Day after day, Queen Otohime ran herself ragged.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.65,0:10:23.13,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,Rescuing the victims of shipwrecks.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.77,0:10:28.19,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,Hang in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.19,0:10:29.89,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,Pirates again?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.49,0:10:31.98,Main,Man,0000,0000,0000,,Help us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.98,0:10:33.08,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,Of course we will!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.80,0:10:35.69,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,Let us carry them to the island!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.33,0:10:39.86,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,Teaching the children of the island about the surface world.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.42,0:10:44.87,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,This is a forest, the place I told you about yesterday where lots of trees grow together.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.87,0:10:47.26,Main,Kid,0000,0000,0000,,Forest?  The Sea Forest?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.90,0:10:49.43,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,Collecting signatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.66,0:10:52.47,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.77,0:10:55.53,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,It will only take a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.19,0:11:00.47,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.74,0:11:03.05,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,Queen Otohime.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.20,0:11:06.47,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,Oh!  It's you!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.94,0:11:09.92,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,You're all people who have signed the form, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.92,0:11:12.01,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,Today, we've got a favor to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.01,0:11:14.52,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,How many signatures have you gathered?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.10,0:11:17.62,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,I have spent five years collecting these.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.62,0:11:20.13,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,There are ten signatures on each sheet...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.13,0:11:21.27,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,and I have about a hundred of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.99,0:11:25.55,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,So one thousand supporters.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.55,0:11:31.54,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,Fishman Island has five million people\Nso I was hoping for more, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.20,0:11:36.56,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, we have a selfish request to make.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.56,0:11:43.07,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,We want to withdraw our signatures,\Nwhich works out at about fifty of your sheets.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.08,0:11:48.85,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,Haven't you heard?\NPirates came to the island the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.87,0:11:55.66,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,They plundered the town and fled the island.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.32,0:12:04.93,Main,Right Minister,0000,0000,0000,,Otohime-sama...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.93,0:12:05.87,Main,Kid,0000,0000,0000,,Otohime-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.87,0:12:09.72,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, children.  Have you come to hear more stories about the surface world?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.16,0:12:17.92,Main,Kid,0000,0000,0000,,Well... This paper I signed the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.92,0:12:19.14,Main,Kid,0000,0000,0000,,Mom said to. {Gee, thanks a lot for finishing your sentences.}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.40,0:12:21.55,Main,Kidz,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Mom said to! {And you too.}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.87,0:12:27.72,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.72,0:12:31.60,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,I did as you asked because you're the queen, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.20,0:12:37.06,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,The humans are the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.27,0:12:41.40,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,We've had enough...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.40,0:12:43.92,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,of your speeches, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.95,0:12:47.40,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,I'm tired of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.05,0:12:59.55,Main,Shirahoshi,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome home, Mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.88,0:13:03.04,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,I gave it my all today as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.04,0:13:05.10,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,I'm home, my little angels!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.10,0:13:09.63,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,I went a little overboard,\Nso can you leave me alone just for today?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.17,0:13:41.67,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Liars!  Every single one of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.98,0:13:46.76,Main,Crowd,0000,0000,0000,,What?  What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.66,0:13:49.41,Main,Left Minister,0000,0000,0000,,O-Otohime-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.41,0:13:52.85,Main,Left Minister,0000,0000,0000,,You're broadcasting to the whole country!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.31,0:14:00.61,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,Shaddup... ya damn Ministah of da Left!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.90,0:14:21.38,Main,Left Minister,0000,0000,0000,,You... Have you been drinking?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.77,0:14:24.88,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,Ah'm fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.88,0:14:29.81,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,Shaddup.  Ah ain't... Ah ain't drunk!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.81,0:14:31.71,Main,Left Minister,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.71,0:14:33.25,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.25,0:14:35.35,Main,Fishwoman,0000,0000,0000,,Queen Otohime's voice?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.35,0:14:38.69,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,Listen up, y'all!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.69,0:14:46.23,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,We... We can live anywhere in the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.75,0:14:51.17,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,In this vast, vast ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.17,0:14:55.44,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,On the dark, dark ocean floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.09,0:15:04.05,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,Why do we all live in this one place? { def: random drunk-speak edits.  maybe we're better off without them } {Gil : Yeah, she doesn't sound quite so drunk by this point anyway.}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.71,0:15:06.05,Main,Fishwoman,0000,0000,0000,,Otohime-sama...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.01,0:15:14.54,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it because there's a tiny bit of light and air here?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.54,0:15:18.85,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,On the surface, the whole world is bathed in sunlight!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.85,0:15:22.03,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,There is a vast sky above.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.24,0:15:36.40,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,Why do children sneak out to look at Sabaody Park?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.18,0:15:39.08,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,Out there in the world...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.25,0:15:44.17,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,there are so many wonderful places!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.25,0:15:50.29,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,We should be able to go to all of those places.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.43,0:15:59.81,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't we just making up empty excuses,\Nand convincing ourselves that we should give up?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.91,0:16:03.35,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,Be brave...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.00,0:16:07.98,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,and strive for the thing we all want the most!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.15,0:16:11.34,Main,Left Minister,0000,0000,0000,,Your Majesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.98,0:16:15.59,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,If the humans are an obstacle standing in our way...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.59,0:16:18.45,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,then let's overcome that obstacle together!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.45,0:16:24.72,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,If we do, then maybe\Nthe children living on Fishman Island today...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.72,0:16:26.10,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,can change their future.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.88,0:16:30.27,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,At least a little bit!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.85,0:16:52.52,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,I left my family behind on Fishman Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.52,0:16:56.19,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder how my wife and kid are doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.23,0:17:00.24,Main,Aladdin,0000,0000,0000,,Just be glad you can still go back some day.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.69,0:17:05.83,Main,Aladdin,0000,0000,0000,,For former slaves like me, it's all over if we're found.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.83,0:17:11.48,Main,Aladdin,0000,0000,0000,,So whether we want it or not,\Nwe're stuck on this ship until we die.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.48,0:17:16.02,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry!  I didn't mean it like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.64,0:17:23.70,Main,Kizaru,0000,0000,0000,,Have your wounds healed?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.70,0:17:25.60,Main,Strawberry,0000,0000,0000,,I ran into some serious trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.60,0:17:29.11,Main,Kizaru,0000,0000,0000,,I never thought you'd get beaten this badly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.11,0:17:35.96,Main,Strawberry,0000,0000,0000,,Arlong, who was imprisoned\Nin Impel Down the other day, was nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.96,0:17:39.45,Main,Strawberry,0000,0000,0000,,The truly fierce one is Jinbe.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.87,0:17:47.42,Main,Strawberry,0000,0000,0000,,You don't see that kind of strength every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.08,0:17:51.05,Main,Strawberry,0000,0000,0000,,It's far too dangerous to let him roam free.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.13,0:17:56.93,Note,,0000,0000,0000,,Unclear Justice
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.64,0:18:01.59,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,Become one of the Seven Warlords of the Sea?  Me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.59,0:18:05.76,Main,Macro,0000,0000,0000,,Your bounty's 250 million beli!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.76,0:18:12.50,Main,Macro,0000,0000,0000,,The Government must have realized that you'll become a huge threat to them if they don't do this!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.50,0:18:15.97,Main,Chuu,0000,0000,0000,,So they're beginning to learn their lesson!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.97,0:18:23.05,Main,Chuu,0000,0000,0000,,Just turn down their offer\Nand become even more notorious, Captain Jinbe -chuu!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.05,0:18:27.47,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,No, I plan to accept their offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.47,0:18:29.00,Main,Crew,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.62,0:18:34.69,Main,Neptune,0000,0000,0000,,I heard about the offer to join the Warlords.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.69,0:18:39.08,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,If I join the Seven Warlords,\Nthe Government will pardon my crew.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.08,0:18:46.68,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,Aladdin and others who want to quit being pirates\Nwill be able to live in this country in peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.68,0:18:55.03,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, if I accept this title, maybe fishmen can get a bit closer to joining the World Government.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.51,0:18:58.81,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,For the sake of Her Majesty,\Nafter I've caused her so much trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.81,0:19:01.15,Main,Neptune,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, and I'm grateful.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.77,0:19:05.56,Main,Neptune,0000,0000,0000,,Though she's in a pretty bad way right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.37,0:19:09.96,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,This is the late Tiger's wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.34,0:19:14.47,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,I believe this is a step toward\Nthe liberation and freedom of fishmen! {Gil : Literally "this will connect to..." as originally translated, but this is the implication.}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.47,0:19:20.85,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,However, there is\None worrisome detail regarding the pardon...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.38,0:19:33.29,Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Arlong-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.29,0:19:33.98,Main,Aladdin,0000,0000,0000,,Arlong!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.18,0:19:43.24,Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Arlong-san has returned!  He's back!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.81,0:19:51.50,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,If there's something you want to say,\Nthen spit it out, Arlong!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.50,0:19:55.25,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,Joining the Seven Warlords of the Sea,\Neh, Brother Jinbe?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.25,0:19:59.71,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,In other words,\Nyou're becoming a dog of the human Government!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.71,0:20:03.05,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,Have you forgotten Brother Ti's words?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.69,0:20:06.55,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,Stop letting grudges and hatred control your life!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.86,0:20:10.23,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,You've gotten soft, Brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.23,0:20:14.80,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure that becoming your underling would be the safest option for me,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.80,0:20:16.40,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,but I'm not gonna do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.61,0:20:19.97,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,Big Brother died!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.63,0:20:23.57,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,I will be reforming my old Arlong Crew.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.12,0:20:26.67,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,And I'll be taking my brethren with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.06,0:20:29.37,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,This is farewell.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.00,0:20:32.87,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,Arlong, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.87,0:20:35.49,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to stop me that bad...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.49,0:20:37.21,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,then this is your chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.09,0:20:40.85,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,Just kill me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.85,0:20:42.26,Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,A-Arlong-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.20,0:20:46.79,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,If you can't, then that means I'm free!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.24,0:20:51.98,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,I am the fury of fishmankind!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.53,0:20:55.63,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,Enough of your insolence! {Gil : Worst. Animated. Fight scene. Ever.} { def: that's Jinbe's special poor-animation style }
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.82,0:21:00.93,Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Jinbe-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.06,0:21:04.86,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,Fine by me!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.94,0:21:21.34,Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Jinbe-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.41,0:21:24.76,Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Stop this!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.82,0:21:43.72,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,Get him out of my sight!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.72,0:21:45.25,Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Arlong-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.78,0:21:49.87,Main,Aladdin,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let it get to you, Jinbe.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.29,0:21:56.62,Main,Aladdin,0000,0000,0000,,You grew up in the Fishman District together.\NYou're like brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.62,0:22:00.95,Main,Aladdin,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what happens,\Nyou wouldn't be able to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.53,0:22:05.75,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,Why can't that fool understand...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.75,0:22:08.33,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,Brother Ti's real intentions?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.36,0:22:15.06,Main,Aladdin,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter where he goes.\NIf he gets too violent, the Navy will take action.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.06,0:22:20.52,Main,Aladdin,0000,0000,0000,,But if they don't, and he does get out of control,\Nwe'll go stop him ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.98,0:22:22.16,Main,Aladdin,0000,0000,0000,,For certain.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.73,0:22:30.00,Main,Macro,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh!  We're also going back to\Ndoing our own thing, Captain Jinbe.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.00,0:22:31.72,Main,Someone,0000,0000,0000,,Macro, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.72,0:22:33.16,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,Let him do whatever he wants.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.53,0:22:35.60,Main,Macro,0000,0000,0000,,So long!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.74,0:22:42.67,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,Damn, that freakishly strong bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.68,0:22:46.59,Main,Kuroobi,0000,0000,0000,,Hachi, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.64,0:22:52.35,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,The Sun Pirates...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.35,0:22:55.24,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,split into three groups,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.94,0:23:00.51,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,and everybody went their own way.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.07,0:23:10.14,Narrator,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,Due to Jinbe joining the Seven Warlords of the Sea,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.14,0:23:13.53,Narrator,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,the Fishmen who had been slaves are able to go home safely.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.53,0:23:16.12,Narrator,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,Just as they are about to make another step toward Otohime's ideal future,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.12,0:23:18.81,Narrator,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,a ship drifts to the island.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.16,0:23:26.09,Narrator,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,The ship carries one of the Celestial Dragons, who see fishmen as mere slaves.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.09,0:23:27.71,Main,Luffy,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, on One Piece:
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.71,0:23:28.97,Main,Luffy,0000,0000,0000,,Fishman Island Trembles!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.97,0:23:30.97,Main,Luffy,0000,0000,0000,,The Shipwrecked Celestial Dragon. { def: any chance this could be "A Shipwrecked..." }
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.97,0:23:32.96,Main,Luffy,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna be the Pirate King!
